            TechModel("Ory Okolloh",
            "Ory Okolloh or Ory Okolloh Mwangi is a Kenyan activist, lawyer, and blogger. She earned an undergraduate degree in Political Science from the University of Pittsburgh and graduated from Harvard Law School in 2005. She is Director of Investments at Omidyar Network. She was formerly the Policy Manager for Africa with Google. In 2007, Okolloh co-created Ushahidi.\n\n" +
                    "In 2006 she co-founded the parliamentary watchdog site Mzalendo (Swahili: \"Patriot\"). The site sought to increase government accountability by systematically recording bills, speeches, MPs, standing orders, etc.\n\n" +
